actions.value: The Montandon is the world’s largest disaster database: a public good with applications beyond IFRC. It contains information about natural hazards (both forecasted and observed), their impacts (also modeled and observed) as well as what actions were taken when, where, by whom and to what effect.
You can connect and recieve the data to use it in the external platform or dashboard using the GO APIs. You'll need an access token to make the connection.
These are medium to large scale emergency operations funded through a public appeal for funds.

These are small to medium scale emergency operations funded through the Disaster Relief Emergency Fund (DREF).The DREF provides immediate financial support to National Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies, enabling them to carry out their unique role as first responders after a disaster.

actions.newValue: The following data displays international and domestic activities of the National Society reported through GO, which may include emergency and non-emergency related projects. The displayed data is based on reporting and so may not include all the activities of the National Society.
